The paper discusses steganography techniques in communication networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of steganographic cost as an indicator for degradation or distortion of the carrier, which relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the analysis of relationships between steganographic methods, which could involve network protocols and networking infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the paper mentions MSE and PSNR, which are commonly used in image and video processing (cs.CV).
